Prime Minister says he will amend the Working Times to give workers three days paid leave a year to do volunteer work . 
  The scheme will only affect firms with 250 or more staff  . 
  Business leaders have criticised the move as 'heavy-handed government intervention' Communities Secretary Eric Pickles says companies will not be forced to give time off for volunteering . 
  The Prime Minister says the scheme is 'the clearest demonstration of the Big Society in action' The policy will affect 15 million workers in the private and public sectors . 
 